# SalesPilot Environment Configuration

This file outlines the necessary environment variables for running SalesPilot in production or local environments.
Make sure to copy this file to `.env` and fill in the required values.

## Core Application Settings
```env
# Node Environment (development, production, test)
NODE_ENV=development

# Frontend Application URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Backend API Base URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8080/api
```

## Database Configuration (PostgreSQL)
```env
# Spring Boot Database Settings
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/salespilot
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=postgres
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=postgres
```

## Security & Authentication
```env
# JSON Web Token Secret Key (Must be at least 256-bit secure key in production)
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production-must-be-at-least-256-bits

# Token Expiry Timings (in milliseconds)
JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY=900000       # 15 minutes
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRY=604800000   # 7 days
```

## SMTP & Email Notification System (Brevo/SendGrid)
```env
# Email Provider (e.g., brevo, resend, sendgrid)
EMAIL_PROVIDER=brevo

# Sender Information
EMAIL_FROM=ashutosh.shukla@theripplenexus.com
EMAIL_FROM_NAME="Sales Pilot"

# SMTP Credentials (Required for Brevo REST API / SMTP Relay)
MAIL_HOST=smtp-relay.brevo.com
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USERNAME=b29ff7001@smtp-brevo.com
# Note: Use the xkeysib- API key for the password when using Brevo REST API
MAIL_PASSWORD=xkeysib-your-brevo-api-key-here
```

## Storage Settings (Optional S3 Configuration)
```env
# Local or Cloud Storage (local, s3)
FILE_STORAGE_PROVIDER=local
FILE_UPLOAD_DIR=./uploads

# S3 Configuration (If using AWS S3 for storage)
S3_BUCKET=salespilot-assets
S3_REGION=ap-south-1
S3_ACCESS_KEY=your-aws-access-key
S3_SECRET_KEY=your-aws-secret-key
```
